<div class="penelope">
  <img src="/img/welcomingcat.png" alt="Penelope the Neocities cat">
  <div class="penelope-Bubble">
    <p>Look at what you built! A real web page, written by you, one tag at a time. There's just one thing left to do: put it on the actual internet.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<p>Here's everything you learned, in one place:</p>

<table class="cheat-Sheet">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Element</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<h1>' %></code> &hellip; <code><%= '<h6>' %></code></td><td>Headings, from biggest to smallest</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<p>' %></code></td><td>A paragraph of text</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<title>' %></code></td><td>The page's name, shown in the browser tab (lives in the <code><%= '<head>' %></code>)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<a href="...">' %></code></td><td>A link to another page</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<img src="..." alt="...">' %></code></td><td>A picture (no closing tag!)</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<ul>' %></code> + <code><%= '<li>' %></code></td><td>A list and its items</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code><%= '<style>' %></code></td><td>CSS rules that change how the page looks</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<% if current_site.site_changed %>
<p>Your Neocities site lives at <a href="<%= current_site.uri %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><%= current_site.host %></a> &mdash; and it looks like you've already built things there, so we won't touch it. Your tutorial page stays saved right here in the editor, ready to copy from whenever you like.</p>

<div class="your-Turn">
  <h4><i class="fa fa-flag-checkered" aria-hidden="true"></i> Wrap it up</h4>
  <a href="/tutorial/html/10" class="btn btn-Action">Finish the tutorial</a>
</div>
<% else %>
<p>Your Neocities site lives at <a href="<%= current_site.uri %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><%= current_site.host %></a>, and the first page visitors see there is a file called <strong>index.html</strong>. Right now that's the placeholder page every new site starts with &mdash; saving your work will replace it, making this page your site's front page, live on the web.</p>

<div class="your-Turn">
  <h4><i class="fa fa-rocket" aria-hidden="true"></i> Put it on the web</h4>
  <a href="#" id="saveToSite" class="btn btn-Action">Save to <%= current_site.host %></a>
  <a href="/tutorial/html/10" class="btn cancel">Skip saving for now</a>
</div>
<% end %>

<% if !current_site.site_changed %>
<script>
  $(document).ready(function() {
    $('#saveToSite').on('click', function(event) {
      event.preventDefault()
      this.blur()

      var button = $(this)
      if(button.hasClass('is-Saving'))
        return
      button.addClass('is-Saving').text('Saving...')

      var fileContent = tutorialLoadSavedHtml() || defaultTutorialHtml
      var formData = new FormData()
      formData.append('index.html', new File([fileContent], 'index.html', {type: 'text/html'}))
      formData.append('csrf_token', '<%= escape_javascript csrf_token %>')
      formData.append('username', '<%= escape_javascript current_site.username %>')

      $.ajax({
        url: '/api/upload',
        data: formData,
        processData: false,
        contentType: false,
        type: 'POST',
        error: function(jqXHR) {
          button.removeClass('is-Saving').text('Save to <%= escape_javascript current_site.host %>')

          var errorMessage = 'There was an error saving your page, please try again. If it keeps failing, copy your code somewhere safe so you don\'t lose it!'

          if(jqXHR.responseText) {
            try {
              var parsedResponse = JSON.parse(jqXHR.responseText)
              if(parsedResponse.message)
                errorMessage += ' ERROR MESSAGE: ' + parsedResponse.message
            } catch(error) {}
          }

          alert(errorMessage)
        },
        success: function() {
          window.location = '/tutorial/html/10?published=true'
        }
      })
    })
  })
</script>
<% end %>
